    "THE WASHINGTON DAILY NEWS TUESDAY NOVEMBER 3 1942 Real Oil Shortage Looms r j V aaMWy s r ztK r m SR fcjgEffrAlwWywty r t 1 J4 IWireMnHilWwi I ift\u00dfMh ft 7V w JH sr A w 4 z 4 aa s K7 A l w4 X V g t 5 x Je4 L x Wf A A Tvlrf r z Z W Ayw w 1 V jt ZlLfZV E 7 z A Special to The NX War demands oil as fuel for tanks trucks and jeeps on all battlefrontssuch as these M3 American tanks in action against Rommel Production Falls Off as War Increases Oil Demands Civilian Curtailment Will Have Only a Minor Effect Editors Note This is the first of twoarticles on the supply consumption and price situation in the oil industry as re ported to Congress by men familiar with petroleum problems By MARSHALL McNEIL The United States is threatened with an oil short age A real shortage that is in contrast to the pres ent stringency deriving from scarcities of rubber and transportation The dark prediction comes from sober and re sponsible quarters It cannot be dismissed as merely part of a war of nerves conducted"
